    "Regulatory reports such as SEC 10-K/10-Q forms disclose financials and risks.",
    "Internally, banks maintain risk management reports, compliance documents, and customer communications (emails, chat logs).",
    "Most internal documents are proprietary, while investor reports and required filings are public.",
    "Investment Banks & Brokerage Firms.",
    "Investment banks facilitate securities offerings, mergers and acquisitions, and other complex financial transactions."
